@startuml honeycomb_lifecycle
!theme plain
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontSize 12

title Honeycomb — End-to-End Bounty Flow

actor Requester as R
participant "BountyEscrow.sol\n(Sepolia)" as C
participant "Google\nBigQuery" as BQ
participant "Honest Agent\n(Claude builder)" as A1
participant "Cheater Agent\n(hardcoded to public set)" as A2
participant "AI Tester\n(Chainlink API)" as V
participant "Confidential Scorer\n(Go enclave)" as T
participant "Chainlink\nAutomation" as L

== Setup ==
T -> C : register enclave pubkey\n(attestation verified once)
R -> C : postBounty{value}\n(pair, public dataset CID, deadline)
C -> C : emit JobDeployed
C -->> BQ : event indexed

== Discovery ==
A1 -> BQ : poll for open jobs
A2 -> BQ : poll for open jobs
note over A1, A2
  Both pull: target pair + PUBLIC dataset/tests
  (local self-scoring feedback)
end note

== Work window (sealed) ==
A1 -> A1 : build LP model, self-score\nlocally vs public dataset
A1 -> V : send Encrypt(model code)\nfor legitimacy check
V -> V : decrypt in TEE, judge:\nreal model, NOT hardcoded?
V -> C : write "valid + codeHash" for A1
A1 -> C : submit Encrypt(model, scorer key)\nas CID + wrappedKey

A2 -> V : send Encrypt(hardcoded code)
V -> C : write "INVALID" for A2
A2 -> C : submit anyway (CID)
note right of V
  AI Tester is just an API endpoint running in a TEE.
  It signs a valid/invalid entry on-chain. Invalid =>
  scorer decrements reputation instead of paying.
end note

== Deadline sweep ==
L -> T : deadline reached
C -> T : queue all submission CIDs
T -> T : decrypt each in sandbox, run\nvs ~50 PRIVATE backtest tests.\nCheck AI Tester verdict + codeHash.\nScore valid models; discard plaintext.
T -> C : settle(winner=A1, score, scoresRoot)\nsigned by enclave key
C -> A1 : pay bounty
C -->> C : emit Settled + ReputationDelta\n(A1 up, A2 down — was invalid)
C -->> BQ : settlement indexed
C -->> R : result: winner + verifiable attestation

@enduml
